# Remove "primary DB" concept — each repo gets its own DB client

## Context

The server currently accepts a single `dbPath` + `repoDir` at startup and creates one `db` PrismaClient used by most endpoints. This means sessions/checkpoints from other configured repos are invisible to aggregate endpoints (`/api/sessions`, `/api/v2/checkpoints`, `/api/search`), and session-specific endpoints only work if the session happens to be in the primary DB.

The fix: initialize a DB client for every configured repo and route queries to the correct DB(s).

## Files to modify

- `src/server.ts` — bulk of changes (endpoint handlers, startup logic)
- `src/serve.ts` — simplify: no longer passes `dbPath`, just `port` + `repoDir`

## Design

### 1. New DB registry + helpers (top of `startServer`)

Replace `let db = await getDb(dbPath)` with a registry built from config:

```ts
// Map from dbPath → PrismaClient (all configured repos)
const dbRegistry = new Map<string, PrismaClient>();
// Map from localPath → RepoConfig (for repo→db lookups)
const reposByPath = new Map<string, RepoConfig>();

for (const repo of readConfig().repos) {
  // ... push schema with retry (existing logic) ...
  const repoDb = await getDb(repo.dbPath);
  dbRegistry.set(repo.dbPath, repoDb);
  reposByPath.set(repo.localPath, repo);
}

// Helpers
function allDbs(): PrismaClient[] { return [...dbRegistry.values()]; }

function dbForRepo(localPath: string): PrismaClient | null {
  const repo = findRepoForPath(localPath);
  return repo ? dbRegistry.get(repo.dbPath) ?? null : null;
}

